menuconfig FREETZ_PACKAGE_PROCPS_NG
	bool "procps-ng 4.0.4 (binaries only)"
	default n
	help
		procps-ng - /proc filesystem utilities
		
		This package provides the full versions of procps utilities with
		the suffix "-ng" to avoid conflicts with BusyBox versions.
		
		Binaries included:
		  - ps-ng      - process status
		  - top-ng     - display Linux processes
		  - free-ng    - display amount of free and used memory
		  - uptime-ng  - tell how long the system has been running
		  - vmstat-ng  - virtual memory statistics
		  - w-ng       - show who is logged on
		  - pmap-ng    - report memory map of a process
		  - pgrep-ng   - look up processes based on name
		  - pkill-ng   - signal processes based on name
		  - pidof-ng   - find the process ID of a running program
		  - pwdx-ng    - report current working directory of a process
		  - slabtop-ng - display kernel slab cache information
		  - tload-ng   - graphic representation of system load average
		  - watch-ng   - execute a program periodically
		  - skill-ng   - send a signal or report process status
		  - snice-ng   - renice a process
		  - sysctl-ng  - configure kernel parameters at runtime
		  - kill-ng    - terminate a process
		
		Total size: ~400 KB

